{"word":"H3380 - יְרֻבֶּשֶׁת - Yᵉrubbesheth - yer-oob-beh'-sheth - Jerubbesheth","slug":"H3380","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">יְרֻבֶּשֶׁת</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Transliteration: </strong>Yᵉrubbesheth"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Phonetic: </strong>yer-oob-beh'-sheth"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Short Definition: </strong>Jerubbesheth"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"Original: <b><he>ירבּשׁת</he></b> <p />Transliteration: <b>yerûbbesheth</b> <p />Phonetic: <b>yer-oob-beh'-sheth</b> <p class=\"bdb_def\"><b>BDB Definition</b>:</p> Jerubbesheth = \"shame will contend\" <ol><li>a variant name of Jerubbaal (the other name of Gideon <u><a href=\"#/H3378\">H3378</a></u>) substituting the word 'shame' for the name of the pagan god 'Baal'</li></ol> <p />Origin: from <a href=\"#/H7378\">H7378</a> and <a href=\"#/H1322\">H1322</a> <p />TWOT entry: None <p />Part(s) of speech: Proper Name Masculine "},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Cognate:</strong> <a href=\"#/H3377\">H3377</a>, <a href=\"#/H3378\">H3378</a>, <a href=\"#/H3401\">H3401</a>, <a href=\"#/H3402\">H3402</a>, <a href=\"#/H3403\">H3403</a>, <a href=\"#/H4648\">H4648</a>, <a href=\"#/H4807\">H4807</a>, <a href=\"#/H4808\">H4808</a>, <a href=\"#/H4809\">H4809</a>, <a href=\"#/H4810\">H4810</a>, <a href=\"#/H7378\">H7378</a>, <a href=\"#/H7379\">H7379</a>, <a href=\"#/H7380\">H7380</a>"}]}